  "22": {
    "Ruckman, Dr. Peter S_": "The fact that God would be the personal Father of every Gentile who believed on Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ as Saviour is a new revelation, which does not even appear in the Bible in a formative statement until Acts 10! [Somewhere along the line our liberal cowbirds have stolen the Pauline concept and Johannine concept of the new birth into God\u2019s family and inserted it back into the gospels (where Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` is speaking of God\u2019s Fatherhood to Israelites). Yet at the same time, they have rejected Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]`\u2019s and John `[char_John_Ref]`\u2019s teachings on HOW to be \u201cborn again!\u201d The liberal offers the lopsided and perverted system of following Christ to become a child of God\u2014to a Father who is only Father to those who are born again, before they follow Christ. It is a nice mess.] The real meaning of the passage is clear. The Sermon on the Mount is an Old Testament dissertation given to Jews, before the crucifixion, to delineate the rules and principles of the coming Millennial Kingdom. 6:33 But seek ye first the kingdom of God, and his righteousness; and all these things shall be added unto you. 34 Take therefore no thought for the morrow: for the morrow shall take thought for the things of itself. Sufficient unto the day is the evil thereof.",
    "Unknown": "And yet there is room (kai eti topos estin). The Master had invited [v_Luk_14_16] \"many\" (verse Luke 14:16) who had all declined. The servant knew the Master wished the places to be filled.",
    "Warren W. Wiersbe": "The name identified the tune that was used to sing the song. Certainly David wasn\u2019t encouraging the archers to practice more because Saul and Jonathan lost the battle, because his song extols their military prowess.",
    "A New and Concise Bible Dictionary": "Not identified. Jekameam. [Jekam'eam] Son of Hebron, son of Kohath. 1 Chr. 23: 19; 1 Chr. 24:",
    "Commentary Vol. 83": "And the keeper of the prison committed to Joseph `[char_Joseph_Ref]`\u2019s hand all the prisoners that [were] in the prisons, etc.] Who, as they were state prisoners, were a considerable charge; and this gave Joseph `[char_Joseph_Ref]` great honour, credit, and influence in the prison: and whatsoever they did there, he was the doer [of it]; not that he learned and exercised every trade the prisoners were of, to get a living by, which is the sense of some, as Aben Ezra relates; or that he in fact did everything that was done in the prison: but the meaning is, that he gave orders for the doing of everything, and there was nothing done without him; all that was done, as the Targum of Jonathan paraphrases it, he commanded it to be done; or, as Onkelos, all that was done was done by his word, that is, by his authority and command.\nVer."
  },
